  <!-- ==================== SETUP GUIDE ==================== -->
  <section id="setup" class="relative py-28 md:py-36 overflow-hidden">
    <div class="section-fade absolute inset-0"></div>
    <div class="relative z-10 max-w-4xl mx-auto px-6">
      <div class="text-center mb-16 space-y-5">
        <p class="reveal text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-[0.2em] text-shell-400/80">Setup Guide</p>
        <h2 class="reveal reveal-delay-1 text-3xl sm:text-4xl font-bold tracking-tight">
          Fresh Mac to live gateway<br>
          <span class="text-white/40">in about 5 minutes.</span>
          <span class="text-white/15 text-xl font-normal"> (unless you're on dial-up)</span>
        </h2>
        <p class="reveal reveal-delay-2 text-base text-white/40 max-w-2xl mx-auto leading-relaxed">
          Tired of installing OpenClaw for your friends and family? We got you. CARAPACE walks you through everything — OpenClaw, Tailscale, pairing — right inside the app. No terminal required.
        </p>
      </div>

      <!-- How it works -->
      <div class="space-y-5 mb-16">

        <!-- Step 1 -->
        <div class="reveal flex gap-5 items-start">
          <div class="flex-shrink-0 w-10 h-10 rounded-xl bg-gradient-to-br from-claw-500/15 to-claw-600/10 border border-claw-500/10 flex items-center justify-center">
            <span class="text-base font-bold gradient-text">1</span>
          </div>
          <div class="glass rounded-xl p-6 flex-1 space-y-2">
            <h4 class="text-base font-semibold">Download CARAPACE on Mac</h4>
            <p class="text-sm text-white/35 leading-relaxed">Open the app and hit “Set up a gateway.” The built-in wizard takes it from there — it installs OpenClaw, configures it to run in the background, and handles the heavy lifting automatically.</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Step 2 -->
        <div class="reveal reveal-delay-1 flex gap-5 items-start">
          <div class="flex-shrink-0 w-10 h-10 rounded-xl bg-gradient-to-br from-shell-500/15 to-shell-600/10 border border-shell-500/10 flex items-center justify-center">
            <span class="text-base font-bold gradient-text">2</span>
          </div>
          <div class="glass rounded-xl p-6 flex-1 space-y-2">
            <h4 class="text-base font-semibold">Connect securely with Tailscale</h4>
            <p class="text-sm text-white/35 leading-relaxed">CARAPACE prompts you to install Tailscale and walks you through enabling HTTPS. This is what lets your phone reach your Mac from anywhere — at home, on LTE, or halfway around the world — without opening a single firewall port.</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Step 3 -->
        <div class="reveal reveal-delay-2 flex gap-5 items-start">
          <div class="flex-shrink-0 w-10 h-10 rounded-xl bg-gradient-to-br from-teal-500/15 to-teal-600/10 border border-teal-500/10 flex items-center justify-center">
            <span class="text-base font-bold gradient-text">3</span>
          </div>
          <div class="glass rounded-xl p-6 flex-1 space-y-2">
            <h4 class="text-base font-semibold">Scan the QR code on your iPhone</h4>
            <p class="text-sm text-white/35 leading-relaxed">The Mac app generates a pairing code. Open CARAPACE on your iPhone, scan it, and you’re live. No passwords, no config files, no guesswork.</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Done -->
        <div class="reveal reveal-delay-3 flex gap-5 items-start">
          <div class="flex-shrink-0 w-10 h-10 rounded-xl bg-gradient-to-br from-green-500/15 to-green-600/10 border border-green-500/10 flex items-center justify-center text-lg">
            ✓
          </div>
          <div class="relative overflow-hidden rounded-xl p-6 flex-1" style="background: linear-gradient(135deg, rgba(20,184,166,0.05) 0%, rgba(6,182,212,0.03) 100%); border: 1px solid rgba(20,184,166,0.1);">
            <h4 class="text-base font-semibold mb-2">You’re in.</h4>
            <p class="text-sm text-white/35 leading-relaxed">Your iPhone talks directly to your Mac over an encrypted private network. No relay servers. No third-party cloud. Just your devices, your agents, your data.</p>
            <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-2 mt-4">
              <span class="px-3 py-1 rounded-full bg-green-500/10 border border-green-500/15 text-[11px] text-green-400/80">✓ End-to-end encrypted</span>
              <span class="px-3 py-1 rounded-full bg-green-500/10 border border-green-500/15 text-[11px] text-green-400/80">✓ No cloud dependency</span>
              <span class="px-3 py-1 rounded-full bg-green-500/10 border border-green-500/15 text-[11px] text-green-400/80">✓ Works anywhere</span>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Troubleshooting -->
      <div class="reveal glass rounded-xl p-6 space-y-4">
        <h3 class="text-sm font-semibold flex items-center gap-2">
          <svg class="w-4 h-4 text-white/40" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M9.879 7.519c1.171-1.025 3.071-1.025 4.242 0 1.172 1.025 1.172 2.687 0 3.712-.203.179-.43.326-.67.442-.745.361-1.45.999-1.45 1.827v.75M21 12a9 9 0 11-18 0 9 9 0 0118 0zm-9 5.25h.008v.008H12v-.008z"/></svg>
          If something’s not working
        </h3>
        <div class="grid sm:grid-cols-2 gap-4 text-xs text-white/35 leading-relaxed">
          <div>
            <div class="text-white/60 font-medium mb-1">Can’t connect?</div>
            Make sure Tailscale is running on both devices and they can see each other. The CARAPACE setup wizard has a built-in connectivity check that catches most issues automatically.
          </div>
          <div>
            <div class="text-white/60 font-medium mb-1">HTTPS not enabled?</div>
            The wizard links you directly to the Tailscale dashboard to enable it. One toggle, takes 30 seconds. Then re-run the wizard and it picks up where it left off.
          </div>
          <div>
            <div class="text-white/60 font-medium mb-1">Adding more gateways?</div>
            Run the pairing flow on each machine. CARAPACE saves named profiles for all your gateways — switch between your Mac, a VPS, or a Pi with one tap.
          </div>
          <div>
            <div class="text-white/60 font-medium mb-1">Still stuck?</div>
            Reach out at <a href="/cdn-cgi/l/email-protection#543c3138383b14243520263d373f363d337a303b33" class="text-teal-400/60 hover:text-teal-400 transition-colors"><span class="__cf_email__" data-cfemail="cea6aba2a2a18ebeafbabca7ada5aca7a9e0aaa1a9">[email&#160;protected]</span></a> — we’re a small team and we actually reply.
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

